items.name: 国风素雅 | Elegant Chinese style
items.description:
【国风素雅】中国风简约扁平插画风格模型

扁平插画风格lora，适用于国风类场景和服饰。其他题材也可以尝试，因为是当作画风模型来训练的，泛化性也不错。配合漫画类/手绘类大模型可以生成极简画风；配合写实类大模型则主要影响人物画风，场景变化相对较小。

适用模型：lyriel，majic系列，guofeng系列，chilloutmix 等

推荐参数：0.6-0.9

Elegant Chinese style

Flat illustration style lora model, suitable for Chinese style scenes and characters .

Other theme can also be tried, because it is trained as a painting style model, the generalization is prety good.

With comic / hand-drawn models, it can generate minimalist painting style; with realistic large models , it mainly affect the style of characters , the effects on scene is relatively little.

recommanded model: lyriel，majicmix，guofeng，chilloutmix

Recommended parameters: 0.6-0.9

items.name: Tonari no Kyūketsuki-san / Ms. Vampire Who Lives in My Neighborhood [Style]
items.description:
A fluffy cute style inspired of the Tonari no Kyūketsuki-san anime. It's a story about the vampire NEET Sofie who's just minding her own business when a human girl, Akari AKA The Dollmaster, suddenly starts squatting in her house and harass her with forced cuddles on a daily basis.

How to use
Prompt as normal, things this LoRA is good is at is general slice of life cute stuff and vampire themes. As a general style LoRA it's not trained on the characters but they're easy to prompt manually. See the sample images and uploaded training tags for prompt suggestions.

MISC
Trained with 225 highly processed screencaps on NAI at 512 resolution.
All sample images are raw txt2img, slightly cherrypicked, no inpainting or helper embeddings used.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist Amatou if you want the good stuff.

items.name: Sophia Loren (JG)
items.description:
Sofia Scicolone, better known as Sophia Loren, is an Italian actress, one of the greatest stars in the movie industry of all time.

140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (s0ph1al0ren:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

This model is just a simple mix I personally enjoy using.

  • Steps: 25

  • Upscaler: 4xAnimeSharp

  • Vae: kl-f8-anime2

  • Clip skip: 2

  • Eta noise seed delta: 31337

  • Eta for ancestral samplers: 0,667

  • Upscale x2

  • Highres steps: 10

  • Denoising strenght: 0,3

DISCLAIMER:

I do not support any indecent images generated of all persons in this model, I do not support selling generated images of persons in this model. please refrain from what they have been posting online.

All persons in this model are 21+ and not a minor, please DO NOT post explicit nudity, suggestive content, or pornographic content online using this model. Refer to CivitAi TOS for more details.

===

Request or Suggestion Rule:

  1. No request for a minor!

  2. The requested should have public data (not private)

  3. Should have more than 30 good-quality images

  4. Since all requests or suggestions are free, I will still need to like your request, otherwise its a work not a hobby for me.

  5. Be a decent human being and leave a review if your request is up It takes you only 5 mins while it takes me hours, electricity, and effort to do your requests.

  6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their hard works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.

items.name: Vore Belly
items.description:
UPDATE FOR THE V2 :
The generations are overall cleaner, there is more variations understood by the locon when it comes to belly shapes and "firmness", let's say. It's more responsive to the prompts related to the belly. Some expressions that were corrupted previously aren't anymore, also. Still not perfect obviously, notably because the style of the locon still often overrides that of the model chosen.

This is yet another locon aimed at creating vore bellies. This one has particularly been trained on being able to render a variety of different poses that might be suitable for the vore fetish.

This is a v1, so it's highly flawed although it has potential. The style of the models you choose will be heavily impacted by the lora (for which I suggest strength 0.7 or 0.8), and there are often artifacts that make it so that several generations are often required to find some clean ones.

That being said, a vast amount of poses and angles are possible. The artstyle seem to vary depending on certain prompts you use, so sometimes you might want to adjust it all so you can settle on something clean.

View the examples posted on this page to get an idea of the prompting required. I used a lot of specific captions in my dataset in order to influence the generations. The prompts related to the kind of "belly bulge", however, do not seem to be responsive, or at least not the way it was aimed at. Those prompts being "belly bumps", "detailed belly bumps" and "soft belly).

"Vore belly" is the trigger word. I often need to put it at 1.3 strength to really create interesting bellies. For the upscaler, I use R-ESRGAN 4x+ at 0.2 denoising strength.

I'd like to achieve a locon that does not disturb the original artstyle of the model used. That seems to be above me, haha. It was the same thing for the last locon I created from pictures of a large variety of artstyle, and the aesthetic that resulted was mostly identical to that one here.

modelVersions.description: The size of the belly feels more malleable. Far less artifacts on the face for certain expressions. More diversity in belly shapes, massive bellies are possible.

It's all trained on the character in the same outfit which is the only outfit she wears in the movie, so it can be a bit finnicky when trying out different clothes, but a lower weight can make it work, if you know how to do it.

Be nice, have fun!

Olivia Wilde as Quorra, an "isomorphic algorithm," adept warrior, and confidante of Kevin Flynn in the Grid. Flynn refers to her as his "apprentice" and has imparted volumes of information to her regarding the world outside of the Grid, which she longs to experience. She is shown to have a love of human literature, particularly the writings of Jules Verne, and plays Go with Flynn.[13] She comments that her 'aggressive style' is usually foiled by Flynn's patience. Wilde describes Quorra as akin to Joan of Arc.[14][15][16] Her hairstyle was influenced by singer Karen O.[15] Wilde added that although "[Quorra] could have just been another slinky, vampy temptress," it was important for her to appeal to both men and women,[15][16][17] and that character tried to avoid the typical female lead by having a naiveté and childlike innocence adequate for such an "evolving and learning organism." Quorra's action scenes led Wilde to work out and train in martial arts.[11]
